                  <floruit notBefore="1650" notAfter="1740" cert="medium">
                     He was a saint venerated by the Ethiopian Orthodox Church, ordained as a priest and later appointed abbot.
                     He was a supporter of the Tawāhǝdo doctrine and preached the observance of the two Sabbaths. He was a disciple of 
                     <persName ref="PRS3886estanfas">ʾƎstanfāsa Krǝstos</persName>. He had many disciples including 
                     <persName ref="PRS1841AmdaBe">ʾAmda Bǝrhan</persName>, <persName ref="PRS10570Zamanfa">Zamanfas Qǝddus</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS4500Gannata">Gannata Māryām</persName>, <persName ref="PRS7560NewayaM">Nǝwāya Māryām</persName>,
                     <persName ref="PRS8710SehinaM">Sǝhina Māryām</persName>. </floruit>
